The Death of Ivan Ilych
Review: This is my first book I’ve read from Tolstoy. Im diagnosed with MDD. Whilst it isn’t a physical illness like Ivan had, it caused a disruption in my life which can affect people around me. How Tolstoy captures Ivan’s pov of the last few weeks he had was amazing, it shows how an illness can take over your life little by little until you draw your last breathe. It definitely changes my pov on life to just live because we all lived once and we should live our life to the fullest.

Review: Personal reflection. I will say that this book opened my eyes to the cruel reality that has been occurring in the US in the past few decades. Even though the civil rights movement outlawed explicit discrimination and segregation of colored and white people, it hasn’t outlaw implicit discrimination, in this case, through the biased justice system. This book resonate a lot especially during this political climate iykyk.
